                            <comment id="14225359" author="posix4e" created="Tue, 25 Nov 2014 23:11:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wrote an alternative registry and connection manager which does not use zookeeper. However the shell still wants to connect to zookeeper NO MATTER WHAT. I can see it for supporting zk_dump but, for some reason even though the shell commands succeed, I get errors scrolling about why it can&apos;t attach to zookeeper&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14225361" author="posix4e" created="Tue, 25 Nov 2014 23:12:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems to be the offender. Why do we need our own watcher?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    def initialize(configuration, formatter)&lt;br/&gt;
      @admin = org.apache.hadoop.hbase.client.HBaseAdmin.new(configuration)&lt;br/&gt;
      connection = @admin.getConnection()&lt;br/&gt;
      @conf = configuration&lt;br/&gt;
      @zk_wrapper = org.apache.hadoop.hbase.zookeeper.ZooKeeperWatcher.new(configuration,&lt;br/&gt;
        &quot;admin&quot;, nil)&lt;br/&gt;
      zk = @zk_wrapper.getRecoverableZooKeeper().getZooKeeper()&lt;br/&gt;
      @zk_main = org.apache.zookeeper.ZooKeeperMain.new(zk)&lt;br/&gt;
      @formatter = formatter&lt;br/&gt;
    end&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14225383" author="stack" created="Tue, 25 Nov 2014 23:27:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did you use &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/xref/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/client/Registry.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hbase.apache.org/xref/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/client/Registry.html&lt;/a&gt;... Yeah, have the shell use the Interface?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14225391" author="posix4e" created="Tue, 25 Nov 2014 23:34:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did create a custom registry. I&apos;d like to point out the code above directly instantiates a zookeeper watcher, even though it may never use it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14225392" author="posix4e" created="Tue, 25 Nov 2014 23:34:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Much like how the catalog tracker also directly ignores it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14225394" author="stack" created="Tue, 25 Nov 2014 23:35:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, as you said. It needs to be taught about the Registry&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14225401" author="posix4e" created="Tue, 25 Nov 2014 23:39:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Got it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14225404" author="posix4e" created="Tue, 25 Nov 2014 23:44:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Checkout this super simple patch which solves the problem. It leads to a different problem that if a user runs zk_dump on a cluster with no zk they get an error. Arguably that&apos;s fine. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
